-- S&P 500 index futures dip after Apple, IBM
-- 
-- Mon Oct 18, 2010 4:49pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/10/18/us-markets-stocks-idUSTRE68J14620101018

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - S&P 500 index futures slipped lower on Monday after quarterly results from Apple Inc ( AAPL.O ) and IBM ( IBM.N ). 

 S&P 500 futures dipped 3.6 points, Dow Jones industrial average futures fell 17 points, and Nasdaq 100 futures shed 17 points. Apple shares were halted in extended trade and IBM shares fell 3.6 percent to $137.70. (Reporting by  Angela Moon , Editing by Kenneth Barry)